{
  "stem": "22869.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Emanuel Mittelman, E-M-A-N-U-E-L M-I-T-T-E-L-M-A-N.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Michalovce, M-I-C-H-A-L-O-V-C-E.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In eastern Slovakia.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "January the 5th, 1925.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I will be, January the 5th, 72.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My hometown was a city of approximately 25,000 inhabitants, or so I think.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] There were about 5,000 Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Mostly of them were religious.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The city was small town-ish, meaning nothing sophisticated as far as buildings, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The Jewish community maintained many, many synagogues in order to please different segments of the Jewish population.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They had places where every segment of the population felt more at home-- so there were more modern people, there were more-- but everybody was orthodox.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The government forced each and every one to be a member of the Jewish community, even though you were not forced to go for services.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS] I would say that most of the population were on the-- of on a scale of one to 10, as far as finances and income, probably 30%, 40% were on the number four, if one would be the lowest in income.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then you had maybe 2% that were high income, and the rest of them were like middle class.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we belonged to, I would say, number four.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Most of us in the city were living among our-- our own.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In other words, there was no such thing as a ghetto, of course.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we were in-- I would say, to a large extent, Jewish people kept together.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Even though we did business with the non-Jewish world, but we had no non-Jewish friends.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Everybody was friends with his own or her own kind.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I would say there was like a-- like a unmade wall between the Jewish population and the non-Jewish population.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
